(Basic Commands for beginner's)

ls Command – List Files and Directories in Linux
cd Command – Switch Between Directories in Linux
pwd Command – Check Current Working Directory in Linux
dir Command – List Contents of a Directory in Linux
mkdir Command – Create New Directories in Linux
rmdir Command – Delete Directories in Linux
mv Command – Rename or Move Files and Directories in Linux
cp Command – Copy Files and Directories in Linux
touch Command – Create New Files in Linux
find Command – Find Files and Directories in Linux
cat Command – List Contents of Files in Linux
df Command – Check Linux File System Disk Space Usage
du Command – Check Disk Usage of Files and Directories
tar Command – Create, Extract, and List Archive Files in Linux
grep Command – Find Patterns or Strings in Text Files
ln Command – Create Hard and Symbolic Links in Linux
alias Command – Create Alias (Shortcuts) in Linux
echo Command – How to Print Line of Text in Linux
tail Command – Print Last 10 Lines of File in Linux
top Command – List Running Processes in Linux
ps Command – List Running Processes with PIDs in Linux
kill Command – Kill Running Processes with PIDs in Linux
uniq Command – Remove Duplicate Lines in Linux

( Permissions )



(User Create, Delete)


adduser ravi ( recommended this command for user creation because it's created by default home directory for user )
useradd ravi ( create a user )
passwd ravi  ( create a user's password )
userdel ravi ( delete a user )
userdel -r ravi ( delete user with home directory of user ) 
useradd -d ravi ( use for separate home directory for user )
useradd -u ravi ( create a user with define UID )
useradd -aG admin,developers ravi ( add a user to multiple groups )
useradd -M ravi ( create a user withour home directory )
useradd -e 2025-10-28 ravi ( create a user with expiry date )
useradd -e 2025-10-28 -f 45 ravi ( create a user with password expiry date .. password expire in 45 days )
useradd -s /sbin/nologin ravi ( create a user without login )

( User modification )


usermod -d /var/www/ravi ravi ( change by default home directory to customize directory )
usermod -e 2025-10-28 ravi ( set expiry date for user )
chage -l ravi ( check for user's information )
usermod -g babin ravi ( use for change primary group of user )
usermod -aG babin ravi ( add an existing user to other group )
usermod -l ravi ravi_admin ( change a existing username to new username )
usermod -L ravi ( To lock any user )
usermod -U ravi ( To Unlock the user )
usermod -d /var/pinky/ -m pinky ( move the home directory to new location )

( Monitoring of User's activities )

( acct for ubuntu 0r psacct for redhart )

(    Installation

apt install acct -y 
sudo systemctl start acct
sudo systemctl enable acct
sudo systemctl status acct  
                                )

ac                    ( Display Statistics of Users Connect Time )
ac -d                 ( Display Statistics of Linux Users Day-wise )
ac -p                 ( Display Total Login Time of All Linux Users )
ac clzadmin           ( Display Linux User Login Time )
sa                    (  Print All Linux Commands Executed by Users )
sa -u                 ( Print Linux User Information )
sa -m                 ( Print Number of Linux Processes )
sa -c                 ( Print and Sort Usage by Percentage )
lastcomm clzadmin     ( List Last Executed Commands of User )





